caption: I was so excited to try this place as I’m happy to see new restaurants in Harlem but this is a strong pass. Food was full of flavor but nothing good. Not sure if that makes sense. The flavors were there but it wasn’t enticing. Also I ordered a salmon clay pot and they put tomatoes in it which made the sauce more acidic then needed. Lastly, the place was freezing. We had to ask for the doors to be closed to which a gentlemen’s looked annoyed that we even asked. Lastly we had a “moms recipe dessert” it was just too much chocolate and additives. Not enjoyable. Our total price was $130.00 for a party of 2 and I left hungry and unimpressed. I will not be going back.

One of my favorite places to eat in the city. I keep going back to try new dishes. The food is made with a lot of love! Thank you Chef Anita for the wonderful creations that satisfy the palate and warm the heart!

Holy. Bananas. This place was SO good!!! Like unreal! Even delivery was stunningly amazing, and you know how things sometimes get soggy or what not. Not with this place! Food was outstanding, delivery was prompt. Order thru their website!! Honestly cannot wait to order again. The spices were balanced, still spicy but not overwhelming.
good food and great place to order from
I walked by every  day, wondering why I didn't go in. Then I went in. WOW! What a beautiful and exotic place. I love the food and the music. A special one!
The cauliflower burger with smoked Gouda was exceptional! Ordering was super easy and the staff was friendly.
Amazing food in a spectacular atmosphere with a warm and professional staff!
The food is delicious and their customers service is great.

I can't express the disappointment I experienced when I found Chaiwali closed. I'd been a few times and was set to have a great Indian meal. Fortunately it was only for renovations. The newly renovated decor was intricate and elegant, a combination of Eastern and traditional. This is a great date night location. They did social distancing barriers and masks required. Service was impeccable and the waitress was very attentive and gave good suggestions for my dinner partner who has a multitude of sensitivities and allergies. She ended up with the Hari Mirch Ricotta and the Lamb. She loved both, which were perfectly seasoned. The lamb had rareness choices and was nice and moist. She was offered samples of her drink order to make sure that it was a good choice and did not have any additives. I chose the samosas and the Vegetable Curry with Naan. The samosas were seasoned but not too spicy with a crispy pastry. The Curry was the right amount of spicy, (I usually have to add, not this time) and the vegetables were crisp and fresh. Dessert was a whole other world. I chose  Alice's Rum pudding. I don't typically like pudding, but this was a delicious relative of Tirimisu. The rum flavor was present up front, with a mixture of cream and nuts that was amazing. I added vanilla ice cream and it wss complete dessert heaven. The Chai was authentic and there wasn't a need to add anything. All in all a great dinner, with great service, reasonably priced, and close to home. Highly recommended.

The vibe and look of this place are what drew me in. The string lights and the intimate-looking front patio made me want to go in, so I checked out the menu and was happy to see that they had vegetarian options that sounded as equally good as their meat and fish options. Also, the music was great and added to the chill vibe of the place.  The hostess and servers were patient, attentive, and professional, though it did take a little long to get served in the beginning. I felt comfortable with the precautions they were taking re: COVID. They took my temperature, cleaned my table in front of me, and gave me my own paper menu that I could dispose or take home with me. The patio was divided with tables well spaced and blocked off from one another, and they also had an outdoor space in the back where people could sit.  I had the kale burger (you can get it wrapped in lettuce for a vegan option). The patty didn't have the consistency of meat; it was its own thing, and it was so so good. I could definitely taste the Indian influence in the spices, and everything combined to make a strong but smooth and savory flavor profile. I also got the okra fries with my burger, which were phenomenal. The house ketchup and spicy mayo were distinct and so delicious I ordered more to go.  I also tried the samosas, which were good, and the Indiarita cocktail, which was spicy, sweet, smoky, and just delicious. For desert I had the rum pudding, which came in a large portion and was very good, but very rich. I could only eat a couple bites of it. I would definitely recommend sharing this desert with another person, or taking it home if you can't finish it. Overall, I had a great experience and would 100% recommend this place. One of the best restaurants I've been to in Harlem!  Edit: went back here with a friend and we tried their salmon burger and lamb chops. The meat and fish were well cooked and very well seasoned, the flavors distinct. Would definitely recommend these dishes for meat and fish lovers.

Highly disappointed! Waited for nearly 90 mins for the acclaimed kale burger...other people were served food who came after us and we did not receive our food at all. Service was poor.  Update:  My friend and I revisited Chaiwali on  10/30 and the staff and owners were very apologetic to what happened our last vist. They also honored us with free kale burgers which were AMAZING!  So worth the double wait!! The kale burger actually tasted better than I remembered, tasty n slighty spicy with fresh avocado....so good. Chaiwali is definitely an experience; so beautifully and thoughtfully designed and the food is really great.  I am so happy we went back and they took great care of us this visit. We will certainly be back.  Thank you 🙏🏽

Great Food! Great Atmosphere and environment to relax and kick it with your lady friend. With live entertainment from time to time! Tonight was my first 🌙 as a guest of a guest. Thank you to all THE staff there and to Jaz for the invite
Amazing food!! Great ambience!!
Delicious food! Cuisine is indian inspired. Colorfully decorated place.

By far one of my favourite spots in the city. The decor is AMAZING, the food is even better! Always so gracius, the owner comes  out to greet people warmly. Thank you guys for a wonderful night. Love Spirit and kate  who served us!

Beautiful decor. At this time you can eat in the lovely area in the front or on the back patio. The hostess named Champagne is a divine beautiful human being.  Food is delicious and on the exotic side. It is not Indian food. Magnificent music is played.

They are open again now and the food, service and the whole experience is fantastic! They’ve taken a lot of care to make the space covid-safe while also still feeling homey and welcoming. I recommend trying the hari mirch ricotta, the crispy chickpea battered kale crisps, and the jackfruit sloppy joe - all delicious! Great to have Chaiwali back in the neighborhood 😊
It's kool

I love this place!!! The food, the employees, and the lovely owner make this an experience that u will not forget. My family had such a good time at dinner that we are adding this establishment to a dinner rotation. I look forward to visiting again and having the carrot buttermilk chicken or the chicken masala nanwich or even the kale burger. You really can't go wrong with anything you choose to get. Secretly the best thing of the night was the veggie samosas but i only say that because i wolfed down 4 of them in a matter of minutes. Also the prefix menu is a good option for people who want to sample the food and not have to sell a kidney to eat and  drink.
Great food and service. Reasonably priced and great atmosphere. Recently redone with a nice ambience.

Ambiance is lovely but food and value need significant improvement before I would ever come back.  $5 for a not good piece of naan and $6.50 for bland small scoop of rice is a joke.  $30 entrees for Indian food?  Not authentic but also not upscale.  This is Harlem and not Tribeca.
Harlem got it going on..
Amazing atmosphere, amazing service and dare I one of the best meals i’ve ever eaten! 100% recommended. Vegan/Vegetarian friendly and super flexible with food substituting. So happy it re-opened!
The food not what it suppose to be to messy
Good vibes, and good food,  will return soon.
Best vibe and atmosphere in Harlem NY, NY by far! Staff, GM and owner are terrific and treats their customers like family. The food is outstanding as well.

Simply one of the best and unexpected gems in Harlem.  Who would’ve thought one would find awesome fusion Indian cuisine this far up on Malcom X?  Each dish had enough personal touch from Chef Trehan bettering any Michelin starred offering you get in the lower part of town, but more sophisticated than any normal Indian fare. As a starter we had the Hari Mirch Ricotta (Indian Green Chili Ricotta), which had an unexpected kick much to the delight of my wife who is a fan of spice.  The star of the night was the Velvet Carrot Butter chicken - one of the best takes on this dish I’ve had anywhere in the world, including its spiritual hometown of New Delhi.  We paired the dish with Naan and a garlic naan, both of which were surprisingly … normal. For dessert we had the Rum Pudding, which is the best piece of Anglo-Indian cuisine I’ve had on this side of the pond.  The drinks – the Delhi Gymkhana Martini (served with bits of Gold leaf), and Ah Na Nas – were good, but not to the class of the food.  The service was phenomenal, with staff holding the line between attentive while not being pushy. The manager, Natalie, did a great job of making us feel welcome and ensured that we come back for brunch at this awesome establishment.  Best of luck to (the awesomely named) Chaiwali!
Love the place, but since the reopen, the prices are a little inflated, the menu is limited. Cauliflower steak was luke warm and the fries were salty.

What a delight that my old favorite, Chaiwali, is back again! I had a fabulous meal with my husband and friends last night. The ambiance is absolutely magical, the food was divine, and the service, warm and friendly.

Very expensive and small portions, but the service, atmosphere, and food are worth it if you're into that. The Naan was small, you should definitely order 1 per person. The shishito peppers were very good but were extremely small for the $13 price tag. We got about 8-10 very thin peppers which was kind of a disappointment. The entrees were great and normally sized. We got the butter chicken and rani. My only issue with the rani was that I didn't really know how to eat it. Every part of the dish had its own compartment on a tray. I tasted each component on its own and thought the elements were bland and missing some seasoning, but once I mixed it all together it all seemed to make sense. The rum pudding was amazing!

Owner, Anita's new menu is outstanding and savory. So glad they reopened and showed out! By far the best ambience in Harlem and one of the most unique takes on Indian cuisine. The food is made with love and care. The staff is very professional and warm hearted.
Coming soon
Love this little restaurant! Food is an urban take on traditional indian food and is absolutely delicious! Cant wait for the reopen!
Lamb chops are the best bang for the buck
Love the food excellent service
Nive place, great food.
Absolutely gorgeous/sexy atmosphere, excellent prosecco, large food portions, not the traditional Indian food restaurant.
Food was excellent, drinks were delicious and crowd was super friendly. Will return whenever I am in Central Harlem.
EXCELLENT!!!! I had my 35th birthday here. The food was amazing and staff was wonderful. My favorite place in Harlem.
It was an amazing experience! Brazilian night every week, please!
Very nice. Attentive staff. Worth a visit. Desserts in particular are exceptional.
Nice and cozy ambiance. Friendly and helpful staff. The Kale burger is VERY good!
Hip beautiful restaurant with yummy americanized indian food. Service can be friendly but Spacey. Has a cool east village vibe.
Place looked nic. , Service was fine. Food wasn't bad, but pretty underwhelming.
The Vandaloo lamb is amazing

Nice food and good staff. Hag an amazing night there with my big brother .  We ended up leaving with moire than a full stomach .  If you're a vegan or vegetarian this is a good place for you to get Indian food.
Excellent food, though a little pricey, and friendly service
Interesting fusion of Indian cuisine. Look forward to going back and trying other items.

So I have been longing to visit this restaurant all summer and I finally did. I arrived around 5pm Wed. eve which at that time it was very empty with the exception of 3 other persons being there and so I was expecting a lot of attention. The decor of this restaurant was very beautiful in every area and clean. The service was not exceptional (energy was flat), I had to ask my waiter what was his name halfway through his service. Now what i'm about to write is the honest truth! I ordered the house chai, Masala fish & Quinoa. My chai came in a metal cup(I thought to myself, maybe this is their style) I didn't enjoyed it, then my entree arrived and when I saw it, the first thing that came to my mind was frozen fish from BJ and I had to ask my waiter if it is fresh....(it was fresh),then the Quinoa came in a metal bowl. Seriously, I did not appreciate paying over $30 for a meal and get served in metals. The food was flavorful but there was something deeply missing which I can't figure out. My expectation was very high and that expectation was not met. My food wasn't satisfying. I will not be returning.  Bonus: after being there for an hour only 5 other persons came in the restaurant and I was shock to see that all the other restaurants in the neighborhood were filled and full of life as I toured the area.
Very nice decor, the vegan burger was really good, the other dish that I ordered was tasteless, samosa's are ok and a bit pricey

It was very good...not going to lie I thought that it was not going to be good, we order an appetizer that was eggplant/garlic and more stuff with naa bread and it was really good, and we had lamb chops and black pepper chicken and it was really good, this place is really nice for like a date
I only had a mojito....perfectly made...staff were super sweet!!!
Beautiful restaurant, delicious food, good service.
Authentic food & vibe. Ambiance that is a challange to find unless you know Harlem intimately. A diamond in the rough with unique and pleasant staff. Favs - Kale Burger and Avatar Salad... Ummm!
Vegan and gluten free paradise
Great food, atmosphere and decor!
Got a cup of tea one late night, and regretted it.
Beautiful atmosphere,  great decor. Food was good but not memorable. Host and wait staff a little stale,  lacking personality . Would consider a second visit for confirmation.
Great experience
Been there at least 2 times for brunch and once for dinner. Service has been amazing and the food and the drinks (including the chai)....just awesome!

Overpriced! If you want Indian food with all the flavor removed, then this is the place for you! It's supposed to be Indian fusion, but don't know what it's fused with! We had three different entrees, all were equally tastless! Samosas were hard, the Goa civic he was bland, can't compare to any from South America! The only thing with any flavor  was the chutneys. A total disappointment!!!!! If I could give no stars I would! !!

Incredible fresh Indian food with an open atmosphere and outside seating both on the sidewalk and in their garden. Very sensitive to food allergies with many gluten free and vegetarian options. Delicious food! We met the chef Anita who is so kind and thoughtful about the food and love our server Eric who is so sweet and attentive.
Good food, excellent atmosphere, vegetables are divine. Bathroom is clean and welcoming. Service is great!
Yummy food, not your typical Indian restaurant.
Great food...Eric is great. The upstairs is very nice but they kicked us out at 5pm...odd.

Iot of buzz about this place, but I personally was not impressed. I found the food to be overly expensive for the dishes offered. We had the chicken pulao and kale burger, and naan.  The chicken pulao (22$) was basically grilled chicken with vegetable quinoa, had no indian flare whatsoever. The naan (4$)was terrible and tasted like pita bread. I overheard they outsourced the naan to keep it non gmo but an Indian restaurant that cannot make a decent naan to me is red flag. The kale burger (16$)was good, but I found it to be flavored with way too much onion and garlic. The place is very cute, but it is obviously indian food for the general fusion public. The service was super slow, and disfanctional , lots of staff standing around  doing nothing , and only one server for too many tables. I really wanted to like this place!
My favorite restaurant in harlem

Not really my kind of food... But try for yourselves. However, it would have been nice if someone had told us that the dishes are really spicy. I'm sorry but I didn't know and I didn't read it anywhere in the menu. That was a little disappointing. Great mango lassi!
I loved it here! The food was amazing and the staff was very kind. Definitely recommend.
Good food and great atmosphere
Food i very flavorful.  Decor is lovely.  I've had good experiences when I've dined there.

For brunch only, might try dinner another day  After all the buzz I had heard it was rather disappointing in that nothing really stood out in any way at all.  The eggplant mash was the only item with a little oomph. The crispy fish was indeed crispy but minimal flavor and the okra was mushy. The omlets I could've cooked at home myself. the egg roti melt was in what looked like a quesadilla, nothing to write home about. The lamb chops looked appetizing as it went by our table and we regretted not ordering it.  Nice decor and ambience is the only positive I can say about it. Sorry!
The lamb chops are to die for 😊

Outstanding food. Great fusion food with sweet and spicy seasoning.  From the appetizer, to the entre and dessert was an experience out of this world. I was dying to try this place. Ambiance is a little on the fancy side for my taste however the staff make you feel right at home. Great mix of crowd from locals to tourist. Definitely a place for a great date.
love their interior. One of my favorite indian fusion joint in Harlem.
Casual, fun, romantic enviorment. I've gone for brunch and dinner, both always delicious food and really great staff.
Fusion Indian Cuisine. Excellent atmosphere. Interesting and fun owner. Great addition to the neighborhood. Excellent and friendly service though on the slow side.

This is absolutely my favorite place in Harlem. As soon as you walk in you are made to feel like family. Big smiles and cheers are never scarce here. If you come on a Sunday, you can occasionally find some regulars at the bar who are always ready to share a story or two of Harlem, life and why this place is their place. Food is impeccible, music selection perfection, decro  breathtaking. If you haven't had the privilege of visiting, it's time you do! Lastly, I recommend to try to swing by on a day when  Eric, (bartender) is working, I can not exaggerate when I say what an amazing spirit and human being! Thank Chaiwali for making me feel at home in Harlem!
Wonderful atmosphere, healthy delicious food served with care for a reasonable price.
Nice Indian fusion restaurant. Loved the food and the modern decor.
Great food, really beautiful restaurant. Very kind staff, but service is very slow and disorganized.
Different twist to an Indian meal
Very nice place, awesome looking terrace at the back. The service however was awfully slow, very polite but took ages just to have a coffee.
The food is amazing and the drinking flowers drink a to do!

Really cute spot for drinks and small bites. The decor is Indian/bohemian, with soft lighting and fun  background music. The area in the back garden and upstairs was especially nice. Service was friendly and knowledgeable, but kinda slow. Highly recommended the mango bellini, chickpea chips, and SAMOSAS (these alone are worth coming here for).
Fun, unique, great place for after dinner or lounging. Love the cumin cookies!
Wow, great food
Food is excellent.  Spicy & flavorful
Great ambience and delicious chai
This place has a beautiful ambience and wonderful tasty food.

Incredible place!  Imaginative and fresh indian served in a beautiful atmosphere.  This place elevates the dining experience, while being completely unpretentious at the same time.  Can't wait to go back.
Really amazing - if you can afford their new prices.

Food was great, vibe is super chill, decor is awesome. Service was slow, prices are lower for comparable cuisine in lower Manhattan at swankier restaurants. Solid place to go if your options are limited
Quality, style, veggies and more in the most delectable home cooked atmosphere. Go out to the back yard in warm weather. One of Harlem's gems.

Service was an absolutely fantastic and unique experience, if nothing else come for that.  Food was well made if slightly uninspired at times, dry samosas, soggy wafer.  Kefir drink was a meal in itself. A must visit

Very accommodating to our party which included a baby. Food was delicious.
Mouth watering Indian cuisine. The house chais are awesome. The decor is beautiful. So why only 4 stars? The service is pretty bad. We waited around 20 minutes for our food, and for dessert.
The lamb chops were amazing and the fish had some really great flavor!  Great addition to the neighborhood!
Amazing food, chill atmosphere, fair pricing. One of my favorite places to eat in Harlem, I pass by the over hyped Red Rooster to eat at this wonderful local gem "Chaiwali"!!

Lunch: the kale burger and okra fries are very good but the tuna sandwich is pretty meh. Dinner: the masala fish is very good and the Anita pie is pretty good too. Dessert: the cake and the cookies are amazing.

Love ChaiWali. Love, love, love. Food, layout/deco, staff = GRAND.   Normally I would mention the pricing, but I don't want to say low cost and infer that the food is anything less than first rate. This has become the goto meeting place for me and everyone I've brought to ChaiWali. If I didn't live in the neighborhood I would gladly travel to get to ChaiWali. It is a special place.
Enjoy the food the chicken wrap is delightful with just the rite amount of spice
